    "• This paper provides a comprehensive overview of the foundations, frontiers, datasets, and computing frameworks of graph pooling methods, filling a gap in the systematic summarization of the field.",
    "• This paper categorizes and summarizes existing graph pooling methods, covering early pooling, global pooling, and hierarchical pooling, which demonstrates the innovation and diversity in this field.",
    "• This paper explores the application of graph pooling in bioinformatics, cheminformatics, and natural language processing through case studies, which validates its effectiveness and broadens the application boundaries.",
    "• This paper provides an in-depth analysis of the challenges faced by current graph pooling methods and dissects the future research directions in terms of robustness, interpretability, expressiveness, etc., which provides a clear guideline for future research.",
    "• This paper conducts a systematic comparative analysis of various representative graph pooling methods, which provides a comprehensive understanding of their strengths and weaknesses and informs the selection of suitable methods for specific applications."
